Compiling
\layout Standard

If you've just got hold of the filer by downloading the source archive then
 you'll need to compile it before you can use it.
 If you downloaded and installed a binary package, or if ROX-Filer was included
 with your system, then you can skip this section.
 If you got here by clicking on the `i' symbol in a filer window, or if
 typing `rox' at a shell prompt works, then you don't need to compile.
\layout Standard

To compile, you will need the following:
\layout Itemize

Unix or Linux (root access is not required),
\layout Itemize

The X Window system (supplied as standard on all modern systems),
\layout Itemize

GTK+ 1.2.0 or later (libraries and headers) --- get the latest version from
 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \cite{GTK+}

\end_inset 

,
\layout Itemize

A C compiler, such as `gcc' (standard on most systems).
\layout Standard

All of the above are standard on most modern Linux distributions.
 To check which version of GTK+ you have installed, run the 
\family typewriter 
gtk-config
\family default 
 command, like this (
\family typewriter 
$
\family default 
 is the shell prompt):
\layout LyX-Code

$ gtk-config --version
\layout LyX-Code

1.2.8
\layout Standard

Due to bugs in earlier versions, GTK+ 1.2.8 is strongly recommended.
\layout Standard


